<capabilities>
The M-5 Caspars had a formidable array of weapons, including naval lasers, heavy naval PPCs, and autocannon broadsides. Their advanced neural network, the Autonomous Tactical Analysis Computer (ATAC), allowed for precise coordination and efficient attacks. The M-5C variant, equipped with the ATAC, could direct up to fifty other SDS drones and relied on the network for targeting assistance. Although the M-5C downgraded its own SDS Drone computer, the additional naval PPCs significantly improved its bow armament.
</capabilities>

<overview>
The M-5 drones, known as Caspars, were the pinnacle of the SDS network and became legendary in the Inner Sphere. Designed as capital-class drones, the M-5 Caspars featured heavily modified Lola block II hulls and advanced drone control systems. They possessed firepower comparable to larger WarShips while maintaining the agility of destroyer-class ships. With their slashing assaults and superior coordination, the Caspars were considered the perfect WarShips, although they had a self-destruct system as a flaw.
</overview>

